item.title: La Seine, Paris, 09/11
item.description: I was able to make new french friends. We walked for 4+ hours. My legs are worn out but it was a nice exercise. A perfect example of nice activity to celebrate someone’s birthday. (Im not being sarcastic - I like walking for hours and hours)

item.title: My Dorm, Residence Lepaute 08/31
item.description: Arrived in Paris. My dorm looks good - a nice penthouse of 12 story building. It’s on the outskirts of Paris, at the 13e arrondisement. I can see the whole train station and it gets super noisy at night. Gotta get used to it.

item.title: City view, Paris, 09/01
item.description: From day 1, Paris, the golden city, was shining bright. My exchange uni - Sorbonne University is located in the heart of Paris, near the station Jussieu. Oh, btw, I forgot to bring my sunglasses and it was super bright, the forcast saids that it will rain next week so it might be less hot to hang out.
